Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.84,0:00:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.07,0:00:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.71,0:00:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.94,0:00:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.55,0:00:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.89,0:00:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,(GUNSHOT)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.53,0:00:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.51,0:00:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond, we have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.08,0:00:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond, we must.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.91,0:00:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.36,0:00:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,(ENGINE REVS)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.53,0:01:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,(TIRES SCREECH)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.04,0:01:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We have company.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.37,0:01:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Ressler.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.71,0:01:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Lose him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.85,0:01:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,(TIRES SCREECH)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.01,0:01:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,(HORN HONKS)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.18,0:01:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,COOPER: (OVER PHONE)\NI know what you want\Nto do,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.55,0:01:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but killing him\Nwill only make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.55,0:01:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Donald, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.26,0:01:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in no condition\Nto drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.86,0:01:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(TIRES SCREECH)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.43,0:01:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,(HORN HONKS)\NDon't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.43,0:01:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(GLASS SHATTERING)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.18,0:01:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(DOOR CREAKS)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.26,0:02:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.25,0:02:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.16,0:02:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.16,0:02:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.40,0:02:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.27,0:02:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.81,0:02:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,(DOOR SLIDES, THUMPS)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.22,0:03:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being evaluated.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Not on your floricultural\Nskills, I hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.29,0:03:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,(CHUCKLES)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.92,0:03:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My mental state.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.52,0:03:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Weecha's sister, Mierce,\Nis a shaman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.83,0:03:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She reads the flowers\Nfor insight into my mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.13,0:03:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I see dried-out and dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.77,0:03:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Bad blood and betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.97,0:03:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this still about Dembe\Njoining the FBI?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.74,0:03:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that wasn't\Nabout betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.61,0:03:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about\Nupward mobility.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.58,0:03:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened\Nto Elizabeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.18,0:03:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe shares a significant\Nresponsibility for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.85,0:03:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you\Ntalking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.79,0:03:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Townsend is responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.52,0:03:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He sent Vandyke,\NVandyke pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.53,0:03:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought\Nyou were with the sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.93,0:03:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.\NWeecha and I are roommates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.30,0:03:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The bed is\Nmuch more comfortable\Nthan the couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.57,0:03:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I, being a gentleman,\NI offered her the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.94,0:03:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She being a lady,\Nshe invited me to join her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.64,0:03:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Marvin,\Nyou said you had news.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.64,0:04:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hope\Nit's decidedly less dry
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.68,0:04:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and considerably more light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.58,0:04:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Hess, Ray, Colby.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.82,0:04:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tuesday, Wednesday,\NThursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.19,0:04:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Three days, three hits.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.36,0:04:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No who, no why,\Nonly the what,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.03,0:04:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.56,0:04:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing worse\Nis the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am the first one\Ntelling you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.23,0:04:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hess was hit on Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.90,0:04:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How could this possibly\Nbe news to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.34,0:04:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You're out of touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.91,0:04:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to get your ducks\Nin a row, Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.11,0:04:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,AGNES: Pinky!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.25,0:04:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.75,0:04:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you a bundle of energy\Nthis morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.22,0:04:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got orchestra practice\Nbefore school,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.89,0:04:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,then a math quiz\Nand an English presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.22,0:04:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm trying out\Nfor the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.42,0:04:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you're reading me\Nsome Pippi Longstocking.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're weeks behind on that,\Nby the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.36,0:04:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,(HORN HONKS)\NThat's Sadie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.60,0:04:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Total frenemy.\NGot to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Weecha.\NBye!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.60,0:05:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,(CHUCKLES)\N(DOOR CLOSES)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.27,0:05:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to think I had\Nthat much energy once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.20,0:05:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, if I did,\Nit's depressing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.04,0:05:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to think about\Nwhere it all went.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.38,0:05:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps this will give you\Na jolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.58,0:05:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems\NI'm under attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.68,0:05:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past week,\Na strike team has taken out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.42,0:05:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,three key members\Nof my organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry\Nto hear that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.05,0:05:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, but I'm not here\Nfor your sympathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.29,0:05:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, because officially,\Nyou don't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.49,0:05:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,On the record, the Bureau\Nwould be thrilled to know
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.22,0:05:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the Reddington organization\Nis under siege,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm guessing\Nyou're not here\Nfor my official response.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As a rule,\NI police my own business.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.46,0:05:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case,\NI need help,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.07,0:05:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you want the blacklist\Nto continue,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.60,0:05:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll give it.\NIt's that bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.44,0:05:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The attacks were surgical\Nand strategic,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.91,0:05:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,requiring an insightful\Nknowledge of my organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.01,0:05:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't really know\Nfrom which direction
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.61,0:05:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this assault is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.01,0:05:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's\None more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe...\NI won't work with him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.02,0:05:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?\NAll that matters\Nis that I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.12,0:05:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll have\Nto be replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.42,0:05:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.56,0:05:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,certainly not\Nwithout knowing why.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.82,0:05:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask him.\NHe's an honest fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.66,0:05:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?\NAfter he tells you,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you may not want to work\Nwith him either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.50,0:06:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,(KEYS CLACKING)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.40,0:06:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,(BEEPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.58,0:06:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,COOPER:\NReddington's worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.88,0:06:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,His organization's\Nunder attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.65,0:06:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wants our help\Nto fend it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.78,0:06:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have a name\Nor a motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.65,0:06:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Only this,\Nthree victims in three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.46,0:06:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,RESSLER: Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ricki Hess.\NJack Ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.46,0:06:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Budge Colby.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.53,0:06:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They were, once.\NGood people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.83,0:06:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What did they do\Nfor Reddington?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.16,0:06:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Operations.\NEach was responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.33,0:06:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for a different port.\NNew Jersey, Norfolk, Miami.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.97,0:06:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,These were top people.\NWell-protected.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.87,0:06:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But yet someone got\Nto all three.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.81,0:06:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder\NReddington's worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.34,0:06:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've asked our field offices\Nin the relevant cities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.51,0:06:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to forward us\Nthe crime-scene information.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.51,0:06:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's a clue in there\Nabout who did this,\Nwe need to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.11,0:06:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We already have a clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.48,0:06:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know who did this?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.98,0:06:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what\Nthey're going to do next.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How happy is Reddington that\Nyou're on the task force?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.99,0:07:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not very.\NIn fact, he wants me\Nto kick you off it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.26,0:07:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NWhy would he want that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.73,0:07:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He said\NI should ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Vandyke.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.36,0:07:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was doing my job\Neven a little bit\Nthat day, that night,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.53,0:07:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I would've seen him\Nlong before he shot Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I could've stopped him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.17,0:07:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And Reddington blames you\Nbecause you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.77,0:07:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No more\Nthan I blame myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.97,0:07:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,RESSLER: You shouldn't.\NI don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.21,0:07:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And, believe me,\NI tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.75,0:07:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond has\NVandyke's phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.75,0:07:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He had someone pull\Nthe GPS data points
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.92,0:07:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,from the day\NElizabeth was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.52,0:07:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I met Elizabeth at a diner\Nhours before she was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.92,0:07:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The GPS data points\Nand photos on the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.32,0:07:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,show that Vandyke\Nwas watching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.13,0:07:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was paying attention\Nat all,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.76,0:07:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have noticed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.10,0:07:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he know\Nyou'd be there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.73,0:07:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I assume he was following me,\Nbut I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is why I had\Nthe phone data sent to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.43,0:07:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that by tracking it,\NI'll find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.14,0:07:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I could use your help\Nplotting the data points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.84,0:07:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.\NSo what's the clue?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.24,0:07:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought\NI was being kicked off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.74,0:07:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my call,\Nnot Red's.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:07:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He thought I would agree\Nwith him
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.08,0:08:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,once you had\Nexplained yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.65,0:08:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You have, and I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.62,0:08:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the clue,\Nlet's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.62,0:08:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a macro look\Nat Raymond's operations\Nin the Atlantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.86,0:08:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he have that many\Noperations in the Pacific?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,DEMBE: And the Indian, Baltic,\Nand the Mediterranean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.06,0:08:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing in the Arctic?\NDEMBE: No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.80,0:08:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than a compound\Non the Faroe Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.87,0:08:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's official.\NOur lives suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.47,0:08:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,For shipping\Nin the Atlantic,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.27,0:08:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he uses accounts in Hamburg,\NBelfast, and the Caymans.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.64,0:08:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Funds are routed through\Nthe hawala network to Morocco.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.28,0:08:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He then ships\Nfrom Gibraltar, Benin\Nor Dakar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.05,0:08:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You really know everything,\Ndon't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.78,0:08:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I assumed you did,\Nbut you actually do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.98,0:08:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't always.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.48,0:08:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything with Raymond\Nis need-to-know,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.19,0:08:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,but after Elizabeth,\Nhe couldn't function.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.62,0:08:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to function\Nfor him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.86,0:08:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You took over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.26,0:08:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I did.\NARAM: What was that like,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.36,0:08:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,going from the man\Nin front of the man
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.00,0:08:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to the man behind him?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.04,0:09:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,(TIRES SCREECH)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.22,0:09:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,(TIRES SCREECH)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.63,0:09:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.90,0:09:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Benin, Dakar,\NGibraltar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.30,0:09:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Goods ship from there\Nto New Jersey, Norfolk, Miami.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.64,0:09:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond is a middle man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.94,0:09:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He has clients.\NThey have goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.07,0:09:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If the port of entry\Nis choked off
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.54,0:09:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and they can't take\Ndelivery,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.34,0:09:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that costs them money,\Nwhich Raymond has to cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all very educational,\Nbut where's the clue?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.08,0:09:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.85,0:09:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The port of Baltimore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.69,0:09:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(SHIP HORN BLARES IN DISTANCE)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.02,0:09:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,(BIRDS CALLING)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.66,0:09:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,(DOOR OPENS)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.52,0:09:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That you, Joe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.29,0:09:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, I know,\Nno smoking on site.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.50,0:09:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell\Nher royal pain in the...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.16,0:09:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,(SILENCED GUNSHOT)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.03,0:10:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What the...\NJoe?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.23,0:10:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,(SILENCED GUNSHOT)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.31,0:10:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Baltimore is Raymond's\Nonly remaining port of entry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.18,0:10:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on the eastern seaboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.51,0:10:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever's doing this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.91,0:10:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,took out\Nthree of his port managers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.75,0:10:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's safe to assume\Nhe'll try to take out\Na fourth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,(SILENCED GUNSHOT)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.21,0:10:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Reginald Lawler.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.14,0:10:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go get him,\Nand hope we're not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.08,0:10:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,MAN: Hands in the air!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.31,0:11:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,(SCREAMS)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.14,0:11:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I think you will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.78,0:11:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start\Nwith the same question
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.35,0:11:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked the others,\Nhuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.55,0:11:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This man,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.92,0:11:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.76,0:11:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,MARVIN: What do you mean\NLawler's not answering?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.13,0:11:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Then go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.86,0:11:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care\Nthat you just gave birth.\N(CELL PHONE DIALING)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.80,0:11:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That is not my problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.40,0:11:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My problem is $106 million\Nworth of goods...\N(LINE RINGING)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.04,0:11:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,...we rerouted to Baltimore\Nthat now can't land\Nin Baltimore
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.34,0:11:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you get Lawler\Nto land them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.18,0:11:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And until he lands them,\Nwe are out 5% a day
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.55,0:11:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in insurance\Nand carrying charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.65,0:11:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I suggest\Nyou wrap Junior\Nin a binky,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.65,0:11:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,shove him\Nonto your mammilla,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.95,0:12:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and go find Lawler.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.62,0:12:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lawler's out of pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.06,0:12:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoo-hoo.\NDid you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.20,0:12:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Lawler is AWOL, which means\Nthe East Coast is shut down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.30,0:12:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mierce read the flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.07,0:12:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Mierce.\NThe shaman?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.57,0:12:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,She's optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.47,0:12:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.84,0:12:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.27,0:12:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The shaman is optimistic.\NFantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it doesn't mean\Nthere aren't problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.38,0:12:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means\Nwe'll figure them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.05,0:12:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you value my counsel?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.72,0:12:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.72,0:12:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.39,0:12:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You've lost your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.53,0:12:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is falling apart\Naround you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.06,0:12:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're all beatific\Nbecause your ex-lover
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,looked at a photograph\Nof some dead flowers
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.43,0:12:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and said Kumbaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.87,0:12:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not my ex.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.07,0:12:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just pausing
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.90,0:12:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,until I resolve the issues\Nsurrounding Elizabeth's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.24,0:12:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That is another thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.11,0:12:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You blame Dembe\Nfor something he didn't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.15,0:13:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth's death\Nhas been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.28,0:13:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Asked. Answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.28,0:13:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As is the reason\Nwe are in this mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.52,0:13:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.89,0:13:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I know\Nthis is third-rail stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.92,0:13:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're the one\Ngetting your flowers read,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.96,0:13:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,so what the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.93,0:13:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You never should've designated\NElizabeth as your successor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.93,0:13:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,She wasn't qualified.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And when she passed\Nand you went away,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.40,0:13:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,there was no one to keep\Nall hell from breaking loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.51,0:13:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)\NSeven days, seven countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.15,0:13:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I am done looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.75,0:13:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you\Nwe wouldn't find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.72,0:13:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, forgive me\Nfor hoping he might not want
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.89,0:13:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,his entire life's work\Nburned to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.95,0:13:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,His life's work\Nwas Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.16,0:13:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my life's work\Nwas him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.26,0:13:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And right now,\Nit is under siege.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.29,0:13:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Chin in Taipei.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.93,0:13:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Madrzyk in Dubrovnik.\NBaptiste in Haiti.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.30,0:13:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all moving\Nagainst us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.73,0:13:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we don't put them down,\Nothers will follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.74,0:13:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I say "we,"\NI mean you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.11,0:14:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.54,0:14:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting with Baptiste,\Nwho's in Texas,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.74,0:14:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,meeting with\Nother turncoats.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.81,0:14:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Red may have\Npicked Elizabeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.68,0:14:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but we both know that\Nyou are his natural successor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.32,0:14:12.19,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)\NNow that they're gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.32,0:14:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the organization\Nis yours to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.32,0:14:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)\NAnd if I don't want to?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.22,0:14:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it gets\Nsliced and diced.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.63,0:14:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren't equipped\Nfor what came,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.07,0:14:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,least of all Dembe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.53,0:14:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.74,0:14:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My point, my counsel,\Nis this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.61,0:14:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You left us\Nin the lurch once,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.01,0:14:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,don't do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.35,0:14:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Marybeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.95,0:14:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell her to stay home\Nwith her newborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.28,0:14:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If Lawler's\Nnot answering,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.85,0:14:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because\Nhe's been captured,\Nif not killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.59,0:14:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case,\Nwe got no play.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.96,0:14:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sure Dembe's\Nplaying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.46,0:14:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe? I thought\Nyou want him\Noff the task force.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.83,0:14:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.\NBut I have no illusions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:15:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that Harold will abide\Nby my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.67,0:15:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're wrong\Nabout Dembe's abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.97,0:15:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,His not wanting\Nto run my empire\Ndoesn't mean he couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe me, if you and I\Nare realizing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.88,0:15:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that Lawler's\Nbeen targeted now,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.31,0:15:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe's\Nalready realized it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.18,0:15:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.42,0:15:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.85,0:15:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Mierce's optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.86,0:15:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.92,0:15:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Park reports two guards\Ndown at the perimeter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.66,0:15:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She's waiting on EMTs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.03,0:15:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no intel on the number\Nof mercs
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.56,0:15:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,or where they are\Nin the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.83,0:15:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A TAC unit is on the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.43,0:15:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not engage until we know\Nwhat we're dealing with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.85,0:15:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,DEMBE: I see movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.48,0:15:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who\Nor how many.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to get closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to give you\None more chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.39,0:16:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe Zuma,\Nwhere is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.89,0:16:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.20,0:16:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,(SHUDDERED BREATHING)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.87,0:16:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,(SCREAMING)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.10,0:16:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe, talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.30,0:16:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.07,0:16:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where...\NWhat is it?\NWhat can't be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.41,0:16:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not what. Who.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.91,0:16:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Boukman Baptiste.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.31,0:16:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know\Nwho that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.55,0:16:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A man I killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.89,0:16:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.09,0:16:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.93,0:16:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.27,0:16:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,(BREATHING QUICKLY)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.82,0:17:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,DEMBE: Recon said his boy\Nwould be at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.97,0:17:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't\Nabout hurting Raymond.\N(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.11,0:17:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about killing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.11,0:17:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(SCREAMING)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.77,0:17:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's true,\NI want you out of there.\NIs that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.15,0:17:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Zuma,\Ndo you copy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.18,0:17:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Agent Zuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.96,0:17:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ressler,\Nwe lost contact with Dembe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.02,0:17:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,RESSLER: Yeah, we split up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have eyes on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Circle back,\Nthen report.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have your agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.73,0:17:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I assume there are others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.37,0:17:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them to stand down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.34,0:17:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Harold Cooper\Nwith the FBI.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.20,0:17:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Who am I speaking to?\NTell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.21,0:17:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I will, as soon as I hear\Nthat my agent is all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.97,0:17:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Your agent\Nkilled my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.35,0:18:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I just need to know\Nthat he's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.18,0:18:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He was 10,\Nsitting in the back\Nof a car,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.22,0:18:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when your agent\Nmurdered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.36,0:18:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a tragedy,\Nbut killing other people
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.22,0:18:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,will only make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.66,0:18:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know that\Nwhen you hired him,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.33,0:18:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that he murdered children?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help you,\Nbut you have to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.00,0:18:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.23,0:18:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not a religious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.04,0:18:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes even\Na sinner's prayers\Nare answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.09,0:18:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that Dembe?\NWas he hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.59,0:18:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.01,0:19:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,(GRUNTING)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.58,0:19:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This does not\Nmake us even!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.02,0:19:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Only your daughter\Ndoes that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.12,0:19:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A child for a child!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.22,0:19:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.47,0:19:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,(GASPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.10,0:19:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,(WHIMPERS)
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.38,0:19:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,RESSLER: Drop it!\NDon't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.75,0:19:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Unclip it.\NFace the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.96,0:19:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,(BREATHING HEAVILY)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.33,0:20:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Baptiste?\NGone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.77,0:20:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he, and why was he\Nso interested in finding you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.51,0:20:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To avenge the death\Nof his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.97,0:20:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,(GRUNTS)\NI'm sorry\Nyou got hurt in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.41,0:20:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you gotta go\Nwarn Isabella.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he was after\Nhis daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.98,0:20:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I got this.\NCall her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.78,0:20:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs to be called,\Njust not by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.08,0:20:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?\NIt's complicated.\NI can't explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.55,0:20:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,202-555-0144.\N(CELL PHONE DIALING)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.03,0:20:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you and Isabella\Ngot past the tough times.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.50,0:20:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We did.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.33,0:20:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Until we didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.13,0:20:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Aah!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.70,0:20:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,ISABELLA:\NI don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.17,0:20:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You worked\Nfor one white guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.90,0:20:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you want to work\Nfor white guys with badges?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.71,0:20:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you,\NI haven't decided yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.61,0:20:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'm here,\Nto get your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.71,0:20:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My opinion\Nis that I don't want\Nmy father
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.68,0:20:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a Judas\Nto his community.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella,\NI know these agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.48,0:20:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They're good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.08,0:20:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I never criticized you\Nfor working for Reddington.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.25,0:20:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I hated it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.69,0:20:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My child almost died\Nbecause of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.66,0:21:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I told myself\Nthat's what you do,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.23,0:21:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.36,0:21:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.03,0:21:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth is dead.\NRaymond is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.53,0:21:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm alone,\Nlooking for a purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.60,0:21:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really\Nwho you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,A Black man\Nwho wants to be a cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a man that wants\Nto helps people
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.87,0:21:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and a man\Nwho's also proud\Nto be Black.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.58,0:21:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I can do both.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.21,0:21:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Reddington is one man.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.35,0:21:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The cops are part\Nof a system of oppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.22,0:21:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You do this,\Npeople will see you\Nas a sellout and a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.92,0:21:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care\Nwhat other people see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.55,0:21:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I only care what you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.92,0:21:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You wanna know\Nwhat I see?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.22,0:21:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,George Floyd,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Breonna Taylor,\NPhilando Castile...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.23,0:21:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I see them, too.\N...Freddie Gray,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.90,0:21:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Eric Garner,\NMichael Brown...\NI see them, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.03,0:21:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and I know that any day\Nwhat happened to them
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.97,0:21:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,could happen to me...\NAtatiana Jefferson,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.40,0:21:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Botham Jean,\NAlton Sterling...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.57,0:21:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella, I see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.57,0:21:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know\Nthere is injustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.77,0:21:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But I also know\Njustice can be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.54,0:21:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen it done,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.94,0:21:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think I'd find purpose\Nin doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.98,0:21:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella.\NIsabella!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.89,0:22:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.19,0:22:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,(CELL PHONE RINGING)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.80,0:22:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,(CELL PHONE BEEPS)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Isabella.\NLeave a message at the beep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.43,0:22:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\N(BEEPS)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.57,0:22:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Agent Ressler,\Nagain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.24,0:22:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I know we keep calling,\Nbut it's incredibly important
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.11,0:22:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that you call me as soon\Nas you get this message.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.41,0:22:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N(CELL PHONE BEEPS)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.74,0:22:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, we sent agents.\NShe's gonna be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.81,0:22:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He got to Hess, Ray\Nand Colby.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,(GUN COCKS)\NInside, quietly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.36,0:22:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,(DOOR CREAKS)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.50,0:22:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella!\NIsabella!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.00,0:22:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, check it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.88,0:22:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,(DIALING)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.28,0:23:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,(CELL PHONE RINGS, BEEPS)
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.85,0:23:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,BAPTISTE:\NConsider yourself lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.69,0:23:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to let you have\Nthe opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.69,0:23:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I never got with my boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.52,0:23:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going\Nto let you say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.36,0:23:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa? Papa?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.13,0:23:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.33,0:23:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do this.\NDon't hurt her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.93,0:23:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no interest\Nin hurting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.67,0:23:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Only you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.71,0:23:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Reddington.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel died because\Nyou wanted his business.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.48,0:23:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can help you get\Nsome of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.54,0:23:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ray, Hess, Colby,\Nthey're middle management.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.85,0:23:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Essential,\Nbut not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.38,0:23:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get you people\Nwho are irreplaceable.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.05,0:23:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Take them down\Nand Reddington follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.32,0:23:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.42,0:23:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I need two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.56,0:23:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.56,0:23:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,(CELL PHONE BEEPS)\NYou think he believes that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.20,0:23:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you're gonna really help him\Ntake down Reddington?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.46,0:23:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He should.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.73,0:23:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.17,0:24:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,...as quickly\Nas you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.84,0:24:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Marvin,\Nthat's what I want\Nto talk to you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.18,0:24:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.65,0:24:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ARAM: Hey.\NSo I plotted the rest\Nof the GPS data points.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.72,0:24:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.78,0:24:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.55,0:24:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?\NBaptiste has his daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.56,0:24:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NYeah, he's gonna sell out\NReddington to get her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.83,0:24:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a joke, right?\NNot to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.99,0:24:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, what can we do?\NGot to issue a BOLO\Non Baptiste,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.73,0:24:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a silver alert\Non Isabella,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.73,0:24:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and let's try to keep him\Nfrom getting\NReddington killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.37,0:24:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe blamed himself\Nfor what happened to Liz.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.13,0:24:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He shouldn't.\NWhat the hell\Nare you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.44,0:24:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get out the alerts,\Nthen I'll show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.57,0:24:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.77,0:24:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know,\Nwhen you gave us the case,\Nthat it was Baptiste?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.04,0:24:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That I would be going in blind\Nagainst a man\Nwho wants me dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.05,0:24:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't. In fact,\NI didn't know for sure
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.12,0:24:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you were even on the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.62,0:24:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or the task force,\Nfor that matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.05,0:24:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you\Nto get hurt, Dembe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.96,0:24:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you\Nout of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.36,0:24:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He has Isabella.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.06,0:24:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Has he reached out,\Nmade any kind of demand?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.53,0:24:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He has.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.43,0:24:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've come\Nto an understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.27,0:25:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.97,0:25:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything\NI can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.84,0:25:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I betrayed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.41,0:25:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That Elizabeth died\Nbecause I let down\Nmy guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.21,0:25:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine.\NI admit that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.01,0:25:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you want to do\Nsomething for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.65,0:25:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,admit that you let down\Nyour guard, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.42,0:25:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, and after,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.42,0:25:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you abandoned your business,\Nand people died.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.72,0:25:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That man's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.79,0:25:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't ask you\Nto carry on.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.39,0:25:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou just vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.20,0:25:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I killed that boy trying\Nto protect your empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.83,0:25:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was doing it for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.30,0:25:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because you didn't do it\Nfor yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.67,0:25:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.47,0:25:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.31,0:25:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And you killed that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.51,0:25:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Do those dots\Nreally connect?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.95,0:25:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems\Na little simplistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.28,0:25:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.\NI have to make a phone call.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.33,0:26:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think\Nhe has any idea
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.96,0:26:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what you were left with\Nafter he disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.90,0:26:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.50,0:26:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I know all too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.47,0:26:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella\Nwon't speak to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.64,0:26:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She says if I do this, I'll be\Na traitor to my community.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.64,0:26:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She won't be the only one\Nthat tells you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.08,0:26:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That joining the FBI\Nmakes you a cog
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.05,0:26:23.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in the machine\Nof institutional racism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.02,0:26:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You might remind her\Nthere was a time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.72,0:26:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when a Black man or woman\Nwasn't allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.12,0:26:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to wear a badge\Nor carry a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.66,0:26:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But thanks to trailblazers\Nlike Bass Reeves,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.16,0:26:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Sam Battle\Nwho paved the way for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.26,0:26:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the privilege\Nof serving our community\Nand fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.66,0:26:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, scratch that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.37,0:26:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a privilege,\Nit's a responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.70,0:26:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,(LIQUID POURING)\NI understand\Nwhere Isabella's coming from,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.54,0:26:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but our people built\Nthis country, died for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.37,0:26:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We deserve justice as much\Nas anyone, if not more.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.54,0:26:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is\Nprecisely the place
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.88,0:26:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where people who look like\Nyou and me need to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.38,0:26:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our people need us here,\Nfighting for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.25,0:27:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,fighting for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.92,0:27:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, in the system,\Nboots on the ground,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.19,0:27:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because sometimes\Nwe're the only ones
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.72,0:27:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,standing between them\Nand the wolves at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.63,0:27:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In my experience,\Nthere are wolves\Non both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.23,0:27:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does Reddington\Nfit into all of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.93,0:27:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't,\Nand I can't ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.17,0:27:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you know\Nwhat he'll say?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.27,0:27:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I don't know\Nwhere he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.24,0:27:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He disappeared one night\Nwithout even saying goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.57,0:27:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure\NI'm staying with the Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.48,0:27:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,After everything\Nthat's happened,\NI may need to step away,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.61,0:27:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but before I do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.75,0:27:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want this,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.28,0:27:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise you,\NI'll make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.16,0:27:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With Baptiste,\Nyou said you'd come\Nto an understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.13,0:27:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NTell me about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.23,0:27:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I can help you come up\Nwith an even better one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.43,0:27:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I would before.\NNot now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.73,0:27:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.04,0:27:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want\Nto see you hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.30,0:27:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You or anyone\Nyou care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.04,0:27:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an honor\Nprotecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.64,0:27:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I have\Nto protect myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.65,0:28:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,RESSLER:\NAny word on Isabella?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.02,0:28:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what I need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.99,0:28:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\Nbut does Reddington?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.52,0:28:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,ARAM: Look, you're gonna do\Nwhat you have to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.02,0:28:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but if what you have to do\Nhas anything to do
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.66,0:28:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,with what's going on between\Nyou and Mr. Reddington...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.46,0:28:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, he's finally\Nfinished mapping
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.00,0:28:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the data points\Non Vandyke's cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.50,0:28:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, and you're gonna\Nwanna hear what I found.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.97,0:28:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Will it help me\Nfind Isabella?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.07,0:28:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, uh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.97,0:28:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it will have to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.87,0:28:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish this could help.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.61,0:28:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it can.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.11,0:28:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How? We didn't get to tell him\Nwhat we found.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.61,0:28:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but there's someone else\Nwe could.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.45,0:28:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe, come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.78,0:28:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so glad you called.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.79,0:28:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This business\Nbetween you and Raymond,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.79,0:28:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to know I think\Nhe is completely overreacting.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.56,0:28:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I appreciate\Nyou saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.29,0:28:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the suggestion\Nthat you are in any way
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.43,0:28:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,responsible for what happened\Nto Elizabeth is preposterous.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.20,0:28:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.\NBut the reason I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.36,0:28:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, what can I do
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.07,0:28:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to help set things right\Nbetween you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.80,0:28:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.34,0:28:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I need the names\Nof his banker\Nin the Caymans,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.20,0:29:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,his arbitrage trader\Nin Beijing,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.27,0:29:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and the arms dealer he uses\Nin Zagreb.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.27,0:29:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew them before,\Nbut he has other ones now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.04,0:29:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.11,0:29:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But, uh, how would me\Ngiving you the names
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.51,0:29:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,help patch things up\Nbetween you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.18,0:29:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.65,0:29:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested\Nin patching anything up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.59,0:29:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Uh, that's, uh...\NThat's unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.36,0:29:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter's life depends\Non you giving me the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.13,0:29:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,(CHUCKLES)\NWell, that's unfortunate,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.49,0:29:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because I am, uh,\Npretty confident
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.53,0:29:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that my life depends on me\Nnot giving them to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.27,0:29:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You know Raymond.\NHe's a stickler for things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.33,0:29:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,like, oh, I don't know,\Nsay, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.74,0:29:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,not giving the names\Nof his top three lieutenants
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.17,0:29:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to a guy\Nlike Boukman Baptiste.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.67,0:29:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I need the names,\NMarvin.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.68,0:29:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I see that,\Nand I would give them\Nto you if I could.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.85,0:29:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I met Isabella.\NShe's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.55,0:29:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(SIGHS)\NI need the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.15,0:29:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is all of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.89,0:29:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ARAM: Dembe plotted\Nmost of the GPS data points.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.86,0:29:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I finished mapping them,\Nthen double-checked\Nwhat he'd done.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.39,0:29:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is every place Vandyke\Nwas the day he shot Elizabeth,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.43,0:29:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,from 12:01 a.m.\Nuntil he, and his phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.20,0:30:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,ended up in the morgue.\NGiven everything\Nthat was happening,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.40,0:30:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,how in God's name\Ndid you think to have
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.77,0:30:04.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Vandyke's phone stolen\Nfrom the morgue?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.57,0:30:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Muscle memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.37,0:30:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was completely involuntary,\Nlike breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.41,0:30:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Or an innate desire\Nfor revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.58,0:30:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to get\Nhis daughter back,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.41,0:30:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe's gonna give Baptiste\Ndamaging information\Nabout you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.92,0:30:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What information?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.25,0:30:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know,\Nbut I heard him\Ntalking on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.52,0:30:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Something about getting it\Nfrom Marvin Gerard.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.72,0:30:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Dembe told us what you thought\Nhappened that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.59,0:30:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This...\NThis tells a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.16,0:30:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not entirely, but, yes.\N(CELL PHONE DIALING)
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.93,0:30:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.30,0:30:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you calling to gloat?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.04,0:30:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Put Marvin on.\NWhatever you're looking for,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.97,0:30:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,he won't give you\Nwithout my permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.21,0:30:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would you give it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.74,0:30:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We can discuss that later.\NThere's no time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.68,0:30:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Put him on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.48,0:30:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants tier-one names
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.55,0:30:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Caymans, Beijing\Nand Damascus.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.72,0:30:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them to him. I'll get\NChuck and Morgan on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.32,0:31:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Baptiste can have the names\Nif it means freeing Isabella.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.16,0:31:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But if he acts on the intel,\NI'm bleeding,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.99,0:31:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so I need to get eyes\Non this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.20,0:31:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,(CELL PHONE BEEPS)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.04,0:31:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,(GEARSHIFT CLICKS)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.61,0:31:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.65,0:31:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,CHUCK:\NIt's a parking facility.\NDeming and Clark.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.98,0:31:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,REDDINGTON: Sit tight.\NShe's on her way\Nwith Santiago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.45,0:31:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing happens\Nuntil Isabella is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.35,0:31:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the task force?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.96,0:31:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go in\Nwith them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.82,0:31:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't trust anyone else\Nto go in for me anyway,\Nso you're on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.86,0:31:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here,\Nand he's clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.80,0:31:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Car stays, you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.47,0:31:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Level three.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.92,0:32:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.02,0:32:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.39,0:32:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.19,0:32:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's\Ngoing to be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.03,0:32:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you bring\Nthe names?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.23,0:32:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let her go, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.03,0:32:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,After I have the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.21,0:32:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me,\Nwhere do you feel it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.58,0:32:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing you are helpless\Nto save your child?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.02,0:32:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I know where I felt it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.05,0:32:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm curious\Nif you feel it there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.83,0:32:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My back.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.93,0:32:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.56,0:32:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,As if the pain\Nhas a weight you can't bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.60,0:32:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.07,0:32:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So much hatred,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.80,0:32:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and now so much in common.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.94,0:32:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You said\Nyou'd let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.84,0:32:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to verify\Nthe names.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.51,0:33:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't be done.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.71,0:33:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If I couldn't do it,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.45,0:33:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have asked you\Nto bring them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.25,0:33:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,(CAR DOOR OPENS)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.57,0:33:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, the lot's closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.67,0:33:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,(SPEAKING SPANISH)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.77,0:33:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't speak Spanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.31,0:33:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Chuck said\NDembe went up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.78,0:33:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.45,0:33:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,(TIRES SCREECH)
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.26,0:33:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.49,0:33:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you kill his son?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.80,0:33:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.20,0:33:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,After Elizabeth died,\NI had to make decisions\Nfor Raymond.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.53,0:33:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Baptiste\Nwas taking territory.\NWe had to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.44,0:34:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I led a team\Nthat found him
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.67,0:34:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and tried\Nto take him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.37,0:34:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But you took out\Nhis son instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.98,0:34:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.61,0:34:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.65,0:34:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that,\Nyou became a cop?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.59,0:34:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.16,0:34:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,TOGETHER: I do solemnly swear\Nthat I will support
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.96,0:34:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and defend the Constitution\Nof the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.20,0:34:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,against all enemies,\Nforeign and domestic,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.13,0:34:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that I will bear true faith\Nand allegiance to the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.84,0:34:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations,\NSpecial Agent.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.81,0:34:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.04,0:34:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't have happened\Nwithout you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.71,0:34:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabella didn't come.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.72,0:34:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The names are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.32,0:34:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You have what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.76,0:34:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let her go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.39,0:34:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing you do here\Nwill bring Daniel back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.60,0:34:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(GASPS)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.48,0:35:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The French take billions\Nfrom our poor country\Nevery year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.01,0:35:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,(GUN COCKS)\NCorrupt politicians
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.05,0:35:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,take from the poor
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.85,0:35:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and open our ports\Nto people like Reddington.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.59,0:35:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about\Nmore than revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.06,0:35:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about power.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.63,0:35:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about taking\Nwhat I am owed.\N(ISABELLA SNIFFLES)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.43,0:35:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What my countrymen\Nare owed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.07,0:35:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.08,0:35:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There are two kinds of people\Nin the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.88,0:35:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,wolves and sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.18,0:35:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The wolves take.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.98,0:35:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The sheep get taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.99,0:35:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,(ELECTRICITY CRACKLES)
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.29,0:35:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.26,0:36:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.24,0:36:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,(TIRES SCREECH)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.64,0:36:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever you are,\Nyou're a little late!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.14,0:36:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's\Nabout to get shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.45,0:36:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have picked\Na wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.71,0:36:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Who asked you?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.82,0:36:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be\Nan alpha predator,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.12,0:36:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,but they only travel\Nin packs.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.32,0:36:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And something tells me you're\Nnot dealing with sheep here.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.76,0:36:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,(GASPS, GROANS)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.16,0:36:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,(GUNSHOT)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.26,0:36:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.16,0:36:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,(GASPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.50,0:36:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A wolf
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.94,0:36:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,would put me\Nout of my misery.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.48,0:36:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.58,0:36:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm an FBI agent,\Nso you're under arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.81,0:36:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The names you gave them,\Nwere they able\Nto confirm the identities?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.12,0:36:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.29,0:37:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,(GASPS, GAGS)
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.86,0:37:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Trace the last call\Nand take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.10,0:37:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Raymond has something\Nhe wants to show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.33,0:37:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.44,0:37:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to see you,\NDembe.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.10,0:37:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.61,0:37:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,(CRIES)
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.35,0:37:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,(BEEPING)
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.72,0:37:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the complete mapping\Nof Vandyke's whereabouts
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.65,0:37:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,on the day\NElizabeth was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.99,0:37:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I know we've talked\Nabout my lack of awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.86,0:37:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and that\NI should have seen Vandyke
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.83,0:37:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,watching us\Nat the coffee shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.53,0:37:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I wanted to plot this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.23,0:37:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've also\Nbeen agonizing\Nover the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.40,0:37:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that maybe\NI was the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.54,0:37:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Vandyke was there\Nin the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.64,0:37:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that I led him\Nto Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.81,0:37:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as it turns out,\Nyou didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.84,0:37:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was nowhere near you\Nthat day,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.51,0:37:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not before the coffee shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.25,0:38:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means\Nhe didn't follow you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.75,0:38:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know\Nwhere Elizabeth was?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.75,0:38:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've plotted her day\Nmore times\Nthan I care to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.89,0:38:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So if Vandyke\Ndidn't follow either of you
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.42,0:38:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to the coffee shop,\Nhow did he know where to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.59,0:38:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone\Nobviously told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.66,0:38:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\Nbut who could have known?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.50,0:38:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I'm as big\Na conspiracy theorist\Nas the next guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.10,0:38:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but this sounds like some\Nclassic Third Man stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.57,0:38:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,REDDINGTON:\NYeah, that night,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.74,0:38:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.88,0:38:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like if I stayed,\NI would implode,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.21,0:38:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'd collapse into myself\Nlike a black hole
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.08,0:38:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and cease to exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.22,0:38:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.72,0:38:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked away and...\NAnd kept walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.29,0:38:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Until I found\NWeecha and Mierce.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.69,0:38:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And they helped me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.10,0:38:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I helped them.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.80,0:38:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry\Nthat I abandoned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.14,0:39:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever happened,\NI shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.91,0:39:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sorry\Nthat I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.18,0:39:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're upset that\NI gave Elizabeth the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.62,0:39:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. It's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.26,0:39:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And perhaps\Nit did bring her some peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.43,0:39:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't be fighting\Neach other
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.13,0:39:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when we have a real enemy\Nto fight, to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.90,0:39:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have\Nto forgive Marvin.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.27,0:39:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a professional skeptic.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.97,0:39:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But someone led Elizabeth's\Nkiller to her that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.11,0:39:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And we need to work together\Nto find who that was.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.18,0:39:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's a quest\Nthat will have to wait\Nanother day.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.28,0:39:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm late to a very\Nimportant engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.88,0:39:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,More important\Nthan finding out\Nwho killed Elizabeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.32,0:39:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.86,0:39:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"Pippi was sure\Nthat her mother\Nwas now up in Heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.33,0:40:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"watching her little girl\Nthrough a peephole\Nin the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.13,0:40:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"and Pippi often waved up\Nat her
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.04,0:40:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"and called,\N'Don't you worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.54,0:40:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"'I'll always come out\Non top.'"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.48,0:40:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That was so awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.24,0:40:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.41,0:40:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.55,0:40:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to protect you,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.95,0:40:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but all I do is seem\Nto put you in harm's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.15,0:40:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you promise me\Nit's over?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.69,0:40:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,With Baptiste, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.52,0:40:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,With everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.96,0:40:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,With what you've done\Nwith Reddington.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.32,0:40:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it done coming back\Nto us? To me?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.96,0:40:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.06,0:40:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going away.\NWith Elle.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.60,0:40:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Not forever,\Nbut for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.10,0:40:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where will you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.74,0:40:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think\NI should tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.01,0:40:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't a punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.17,0:40:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about you\Nbeing a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.58,0:40:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.74,0:40:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, really, it's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.61,0:40:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I was upset with you\Nabout that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.21,0:40:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd be lying if I said\NI still wasn't upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.18,0:40:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can be\Na police officer
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.02,0:40:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and a man\Nwho's proud to be Black.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.42,0:40:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that because I know\Nthat's who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.33,0:41:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to feel safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.63,0:41:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want us\Nto be together.\NI've missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.73,0:41:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\NI've missed you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.77,0:41:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I see Elle\Nbefore you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.37,0:41:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.77,0:41:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was reading her a story.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.04,0:41:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure she'd love for you\Nto finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.88,0:41:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,"'You have plenty of courage,\NI am sure,' answered Oz.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.38,0:41:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"'All you need\Nis confidence in yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.19,0:41:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,"'There is no living thing\Nthat is not afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.73,0:41:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"'when it faces danger.'"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.66,0:41:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Her father,\NPippi had not forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.63,0:41:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"he was a sea captain\Nwho sailed\Non the great ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.77,0:41:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,"and Pippi had sailed with him\Nin his ship
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.30,0:41:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,"until one day,\Nher father blew overboard
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.61,0:41:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"in a storm\Nand disappeared."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.41,0:41:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"'True courage is in facing\Ndanger when you are afraid,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.04,0:41:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"'and that kind of courage\Nyou have in plenty.'
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.45,0:41:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"'Perhaps I have,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.12,0:42:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"'but I'm scared\Njust the same,'\Nsaid the Lion."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.92,0:42:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"But Pippi\Nwas absolutely certain that\Nhe would come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.09,0:42:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"She would never believe\Nthat he had drowned.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.29,0:42:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"She was sure he had floated
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.09,0:42:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"until he landed on an island\Ninhabited by cannibals.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.26,0:42:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"And she thought\Nhe had become\Nthe king of all the cannibals
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.03,0:42:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"and went around\Nwith a golden crown
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.30,0:42:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"on his head\Nall day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.00,0:42:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,"'My papa is a cannibal king,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.71,0:42:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,"'it certainly isn't\Nevery child\Nwho has such a stylish...'"
